<DOC><DOCNO> AP900808-0215 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-08-08-90 1448EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r f BC-Magma-Bonuses     08-08 0164</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Magma-Bonuses,0171</SECOND><HEAD>Copper Firm Awards $1,000 Bonuses to 3,000 Workers</HEAD><DATELINE>TUCSON, Ariz. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The Magma Copper Co. will give more than3,000 hourly employees $1,000 each in bonuses for helping thecompany achieve record earnings, management and union spokesmen say.   The company will give the workers two $500 bonuses, the firstnext week and the second near Christmas, the spokesmen said Tuesday.   Magma spokesman Frank Harris said the bonuses were a way of``thanking employees for helping Magma achieve significantimprovement in operations over the last 12 months, since thesigning of the current labor agreement.''   Don Shelton, president of united Steelworkers Local 937, saidthe action is ``a real indication of the spirit of cooperation thathas been generated here. It is going to be a real boost ineverybody's credibility.''   He said union leaders suggested the idea of a bonus last monthto Magma's president and chief executive officer, J. BurgessWinter, after Magma announced record earnings and increasedproductivity.</TEXT></DOC>